[h3 id=DumpingAvi 
	" Dumping AVI
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"We imply you already know, that you can not just capture your play to AVI in real time, but to record an emulator movie and play it back, capturing AVI from this. We have a video dumping guide for TASable emulators:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	(__wikiLink|href=/EncodingGuide/VideoDumping|implicitdisplaytext=Encoding Guide / Video Dumping)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"After you do the above, you get prompted to choose and configure the codec. You can use a lossless one (good for upscaling) or a lossy one (fast and compressing heavier).
	$LF
]div
[div class= 
	[div class= 
		[ul class=nav nav-tabs role=tablist 
			[li class=nav-item 
				[a class=active nav-link data-bs-toggle=tab href=#tabs-1471-0 
					"x264vfw
				]a
			]li
			[li class=nav-item 
				[a class=nav-link data-bs-toggle=tab href=#tabs-1471-1 
					"CamStudio
				]a
			]li
			[li class=nav-item 
				[a class=nav-link data-bs-toggle=tab href=#tabs-1471-2 
					"Lagarith
				]a
			]li
		]ul
	]div
	[div class=tab-content 
		[div class=tab-pane fade active show id=tabs-1471-0 
			[ul 
				[li 
					" Preset: Ultrafast 
					$LF
				]li
				[li 
					" Tuning: Animation 
					$LF
				]li
				[li 
					" Rate control: Single pass - ratefactor-based 
					$LF
				]li
				[li 
					" Ratefactor: experiment with it. 
					$LF
				]li
				[li 
					" Zero latency must be checked!
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
		]div
		[div class=tab-pane fade id=tabs-1471-1 
			[ul 
				[li 
					" Check 
					[b 
						"GZIP
					]b
					" rediobutton
					$LF
				]li
				[li 
					" Select the desired compression 
					[b 
						"Level
					]b
					" (start from Level 5, that leaves room for speeding up the emulator)
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
		]div
		[div class=tab-pane fade id=tabs-1471-2 
			[ul 
				[li 
					" Check 
					[b 
						"Enable Null Frames
					]b
					$LF
				]li
				[li 
					" Check 
					[b 
						"Use Multithreading
					]b
					$LF
				]li
				[li 
					" Select 
					[b 
						"Mode
					]b
					": RGB (Default)
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
		]div
	]div
]div
[h3 id=Editing 
	" Editing
	$LF
]h3
[div class= 
	[div class= 
		[ul class=nav nav-tabs role=tablist 
			[li class=nav-item 
				[a class=active nav-link data-bs-toggle=tab href=#tabs-1969-0 
					"VirtualDub
				]a
			]li
			[li class=nav-item 
				[a class=nav-link data-bs-toggle=tab href=#tabs-1969-1 
					"AviSynth 
				]a
			]li
		]ul
	]div
	[div class=tab-content 
		[div class=tab-pane fade active show id=tabs-1969-0 
			[ul 
				[li 
					" Drag the dump to VD
					$LF
					[ul 
						[li 
							" If the dump consists of several segments with the same video parameters, go to File -> Append AVI segment and select your 
							[b 
								"second
							]b
							" segment. VD will automatically import them all.
							$LF
						]li
					]ul
				]li
				[li 
					" Video -> Filters -> Add: resize. Filter mode: Nearest neigbour. New size -> Relative: 200 (300, 400, anything you want)
					$LF
					[ul 
						[li 
							" If you want to upload to youtube and preserve framerate above 30, upscale the height to 720 pixels or higher.
							$LF
						]li
					]ul
				]li
			]ul
			[div class=p 
				"There's no simple function in VD for subtitles. Use AviSynth for that.
				$LF
			]div
		]div
		[div class=tab-pane fade id=tabs-1969-1 
			[div class=p 
				"Create a text file with the following text and change its extension to 
				[code 
					".avs
				]code
				":
				$LF
			]div
			[pre 
				[code class=language-shell 
					$UNPRINTABLE TEXT!!!
				]code
			]pre
			[div class=p 
				"Put your movie to the same folder, change the AVISource parameter to match its name, edit or remove the lines you don't need (adjust the 
				[a href=http://avisynth.org/mediawiki/Subtitles rel=noopener external nofollow 
					"subtitles
				]a
				"), still drag the script file to VirtualDub.
				$LF
			]div
		]div
	]div
]div
[div class=p 
	"In the VD menu:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Video -> Compression -> x264vfw (if upscaled, you can use ratefactor 15-20)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" File -> Save as AVI
		$LF
	]li
]ul
